/td><td style='padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #3f3f46;'>Time: 125ms<br/>Mix: 20%</td></tr> <tr><td style='padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #3f3f46;'>Reverb: Vintage Spring</td><td style='padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #3f3f46;'>Decay: 2.0s<br/>Mix: 20%</td><td style='padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #3f3f46;'>Decay: 2.0s<br/>Mix: 20%</td></tr> <tr><td style='padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #3f3f46;'>EQ: FOH Global Cut</td><td style='padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #3f3f46;'>HPF: 100Hz<br/>LPF: 6500Hz<br/>Output: -3.0dB</td><td style='padding: 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid #3f3f46;'>HPF: 100Hz<br/>LPF: 6500Hz<br/>Output: -3.0dB</td></tr> </tbody> </table>\",\"agent_impact\":[\"<strong>Agent 1 (Tone Historian):</strong> Identified the historical target tone components, strictly specifying the Fender Blackface Vibroverb amp, an Ibanez TS-808 Tube Screamer, a 1x15 JBL D130F speaker, and a Shure SM57 microphone.\",\"<strong>Agent 2 (Sonic Profiler):</strong> Extracted crucial acoustic parameters from the target tone, establishing a 720Hz peak frequency, symmetrical soft clipping for the overdrive, a vintage spring reverb profile, and a targeted noise gate threshold of -65dB.\",\"<strong>Agent 3 (Scraper):</strong> Translated historical hardware into Quad Cortex specific block equivalents (Green 808, US Vibra 40) and provided invaluable community warnings to retain high headroom by keeping the Green 808 drive incredibly low and the Amp bass reduced.\",\"<strong>Agent 4 (Librarian):</strong> Validated the Green 808 overdrive block against the local block database, but incorrectly dropped the primary amplifier, cabinet, and microphone blocks due to exact-string mismatching constraints.\",\"<strong>Agent 5 (Navigator):</strong> Strictly enforced the user's explicit parameter constraint to disable Cloud Sourcing, which actively prevented the system from automatically searching the Cortex Cloud to resolve the Librarian's missing amp/cab captures.\",\"<strong>Agent 6 (Acoustician):</strong> Designed precise mixing and leveling constants, setting the input gain to -3.0dB, calculating the core amp equalization (Bass 3.2, Mid 6.8, Treble 5.5), and formulating a Chameleon Pre-EQ with a 200Hz Low Shelf and 4.5kHz LPF to optimize the overdrive push.\",\"<strong>Agent 7 (Transducer):</strong> Configured a studio-grade dual microphone array on the target cabinet, positioning Mic 1 at the Cap Edge On Axis (X: 1.5, Y: 0.5) and Mic 2 at the Cone Mid Off Axis (X: 3.0, Y: 2.0) with an exact 65% blend ratio.\",\"<strong>Agent 8 (FOH):</strong> Programmed final mix-ready global equalization constraints, executing surgical frequency boundaries with a 100Hz HPF and a 6500Hz LPF, alongside a -3.0dB post-lane output adjustment.\",\"<strong>Agent 9 (Mix):</strong> Defined the temporal and spatial environment for the preset, locking in a 125ms delay time, a 2.0-second decay for the vintage spring reverb, and dialing both to a 20% mix ratio.\",\"<strong>Agent 10 (Map):</strong> Generated the fundamental routing matrix for Scene A (Rhythm) and Scene B (Lead), though it blindly propagated the Librarian's critical missing amp block error directly into the data tree, forcing EQ processing down to the output node.\",\"<strong>Agent 11 (DSP):</strong> Assigned the verified spatial grid coordinates, successfully placing the Green 808 overdrive in Lane 1, completing the raw state mapping just prior to final architectural evaluation, constraint correction, and payload injection.\"]}"
